PHISHING INDICATORS IDENTIFIED:

1. Suspicious Sender Address
   - Display name claims to be “Bank Support Team”
   - Actual email: support@secure-verification.com (not official bank domain)

2. Domain Mismatch
   - Sender domain does not match the bank’s authentic domain.

3. Urgent or Threatening Language
   - "Your account will be closed in 24 hours"
   - Attempts to create panic and force immediate action.

4. Suspicious / Mismatched Links
   - Text shows “https://bankofindia.com/verify”
   - Hover URL points to “http://verify-account-security.xyz/login”

5. Spelling and Grammar Errors
   - Examples: "acount", "will terminated", etc.

6. Unexpected Attachments
   - HTML file pretending to be an account verification form.

7. Failed Email Authentication Checks (SPF/DKIM/DMARC)
   - SPF: FAIL
   - DKIM: NONE
   - DMARC: FAIL

8. Abnormal IP Address in Email Header
   - Email originates from unknown host: 185.202.xx.xx
   - IP location unrelated to the claimed organization.

9. Return-Path Mismatch
   - return-path domain ≠ from domain.

10. Use of Generic Greeting
   - “Dear Valued Customer” instead of the user’s real name.

11. Suspicious X-Mailer
   - PHPMailer 5.2.22 (commonly used in phishing scripts).

12. Poorly Formatted Email Body
   - Inconsistent spacing, unnatural language.

13. Missing Contact Details
   - No official bank phone, address, footer signature.

14. Unusual Request
   - Asking users to verify identity via link (banks do NOT do this).

15. Lack of HTTPS in Real URL
   - Hover URL uses HTTP instead of HTTPS.

END OF REPORT
